H0.text: Silkworms feed on the leaves of which tree. Oak

H1.text: Silkworms feed on the leaves of which tree. Eucalyptus

H2.text: Silkworms feed on the leaves of which tree. Willow

H3.text: Silkworms feed on the leaves of which tree. Mulbery

A4.text: Mulberry leaves, particularly those of the white mulberry, are ecologically important as the sole food source of the silkworm (Bombyx mori, named after the mulberry genus Morus).

A5.text: The wild silk moth also eats mulberry.
